Program: Last Word
Title: Barry Norman, Gordon Wilson, Geri Allen, John Thompson, Jack O'Neill
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08wr9g8
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 9 Jul 2017
Matthew Bannister on Barry Norman - best known for presenting the BBC television's Film programme,on radio he also fronted the Today Programme and the News Quiz. Gordon Wilson, the leader who re-built the Scottish National Party after electoral defeat and internal division. Jazz pianist and composer Geri Allen who played in a wide range of styles and was committed to the advancement of women in jazz. John Thompson, the regulator who presided over the introduction of independent local radio in the UK. And Jack O'Neill who made a successful business out of his obsession with surfing. Producer: Neil George. Show less